## Triage checklist

1. Open the audit in Tron; confirm id and status match the table above.
2. Work **High** first: open each finding, read description + suggested fix, open the cited file at the line in **this** repo.
3. Label each item: **true positive** (fix here), **false positive / accepted risk** (one-line rationale), or **needs design** (ticket).
4. Prefer one PR per root cause (e.g. repeated Dockerfile pattern) over dozens of one-line edits.
5. Re-run Tron audit when ready; update this file’s snapshot table.

